com.hp.autonomy.aci.content.identifier.stateid

Class Range

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hp.autonomy.aci.content.identifier.stateid.AbstractStateRange
      • com.hp.autonomy.aci.content.identifier.stateid.Range
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StateRange

    public class Range
extends AbstractStateRange
    Range is a simple implementation of StateRange that only allows for a single continuous range. It also provides methods for doing paging.

      • next

        public Range next()
        Creates a new range instance for the next page. The size of the new range will be the same as the current range but it will start with the document that immediately follows the end of this range.
        Returns:
        The range of the next page

      • size

        public int size()
        Description copied from interface: StateRange
        The size of the range. For example, the range [5-7,12] has a size of 4. Note that a size of 0 signifies a range that will match all the documents in a stored state rather than one that will match no documents.
        Returns:
        The size of the range
